  &lt;Comment&gt;
    &lt;Title&gt;Change for the worse!&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;321321&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;I've been a patient of the BFOP since August 1997! - and after 22 years I know how lucky I am to profit from care, kindness received from every member of the staff. The friendly atmosphere of BFOP from the minute you check in at Reception, called for your blood test and seen a doctor - it's more like being in a Club among friends.
It's ALL changed today. After 22 years for the first time I was sent down to the basement to a most unfriendly large waiting area - with NO hospital staff present - where a large number of patients were sitting (more in numbers than ever seen in BFOP) pointing towards a wall, where I was supposed to take a number from a machine - just like in my local supermarket's fish counter - and watch an other wall for my digital number to appear. For all those years a smiling nurse called me by my first name - I wasn't a number. Through my two decades coming for a blood test never waited more than 15-20 minutes. Today my number came up after 1 hour and 10 minutes In other words 10 minutes after I was supposed to see my doctor!
Part of the blood test procedure includes providing urine sample. At BFOP the toilet is opposite the chair where the blood is taken. In the new place a Nurse had walk with me through one corridor to another to show the facility. (not to speak of the wheelchair user patients!?)
By the time arrived upstairs to BFOP, I should have finished my visit.
Through the years ny routine monitoring appointments were always completed with TWO hours parking. Today, for the first time I had to pay for THREE hours.
From the patient's point of view changing the location was a big mistake. Maybe this looked good at meetings for various logistics, but for us giving up the first sensation of the friendly atmosphere of arriving at BFOP reception, would be sadly missed.&lt;/CommentText&gt;
